<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="813" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="105.[2007,2602,2955,3377]" box="[2009,2602,3069,3102]" pageId="105" pageNumber="813">Spermophilus taurensis diverged from S. citel-</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[2007,2602,2955,3377]" pageId="105" pageNumber="813">lus ¢.2-5 million years ago. Until recently,it was included in S. xanthoprymnus but is now listed as a separate species. Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="813" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="813" targetBox="[390,394,929,950]" targetPageId="106">
<paragraph blockId="105.[2007,2602,2955,3377]" pageId="105" pageNumber="813">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2008,2184,3226,3259]" pageId="105" pageNumber="813">Distribution.</emphasis>
Erenkaya to Morca Yaylasi and Salamut Plateau to Mut, in the Taurus Mts, S Turkey.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="106" lastPageNumber="814" pageId="105" pageNumber="813" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="105.[2007,2602,2955,3377]" lastBlockId="105.[1397,2600,3389,3457]" pageId="105" pageNumber="813">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2009,2284,3344,3377]" pageId="105" pageNumber="813">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body mean 201 mm (females), tail mean 61 mm (females); weight mean 201 g (females). No measurements available for males. Dorsum of the Tauren Ground Squirrel is grizzled
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="106.[185,1392,291,951]" pageId="106" pageNumber="814">straw yellow, flecked with dark brown to black and suffusion of red. Cheeks, chin, and small post-auricular patches are buff. Feet are pale buff, and soles are hairy. Tail is broad, reddish, and paler below than above butis distinctly blackish toward tip.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[187,972,405,438]" pageId="106" pageNumber="814" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="106.[185,1392,291,951]" box="[187,972,405,438]" pageId="106" pageNumber="814">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[187,298,405,438]" pageId="106" pageNumber="814">Habitat.</emphasis>
Montane habitats above elevations of ¢.1000 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
